Kathrada was initially admitted for dehydration, but doctors later picked up the clot, which has subsequently been removed. JOHANNESBURG African National Congress (ANC) struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada is in a stable condition at the Johannesburg Hospital following a surgery relating to blood clotting in his brain.The 87-year-old was initially admitted yesterday for dehydration, but doctors later picked up the clot, which has subsequently been removed.Director of the Ahmed Kathrada Foundation, Neeshan Balton, says despite being ill prior to the operation, the struggle veteran is in good spirits.Balton is calling upon friends and comrades to continue praying for him. The foundation wishes Ahmed Kathrada a speedy recovery. The surgeon was pleased with Mr Kathrada s condition. 